4
, pH 7.2). The test compound or control solution is added in a 1 Î¼L volume. Reactions are started by adding 50 Î¼L of microsomes (1.25 mg/mL). The plates 

 are mixed and after 15 min incubation on a heating block (25 
0
C), the reactions are stopped by the addition of 10 Î¼L 60% PCA. An aliquot of 100 Î¼L is then transferred to a filter plate pretreated with charcoal and the plate centrifuged at 4000 rpm for 1 minute. The flow through containing the 
3
